# Enhanced Campaign Mapping UI (Email-First UX)

This plan focuses on improving the Campaign Mapping experience by integrating Account Emails as a primary identifier, allowing for better organization and searchability when managing large numbers of ad accounts.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] [ProjectAnalytics](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/adecosmvp/frontend/src/components/ProjectAnalytics.jsx)

- **Data Enrichment**: Enrich the campaigns list with `accountEmail` and `platform` information from the `AdsContext`.
- **Search Logic Update**: Extend the search function to include `accountEmail`.
- **UI UX Overhaul**:
  - **Grouped View**: Implement an optional "Grouped by Account" view in the selection modal.
  - **Account Badges**: Display platform icons (Google, Meta, TikTok) and emails prominently on each campaign card.
  - **Premium Aesthetics**: 
    - Use a sleek, glassmorphism design for the selection modal.
    - Add subtle entry animations for search results.
    - Improve typography and spacing to match the premium dashboard aesthetic.
- **Linked List Polish**: Show the owner email in the "Currently Linked" section for immediate context.

## Design Details

- **Campaign Card**: 
  - Title: Campaign Name (Bold)
  - Subtitle: Program Name | Platform
  - Footer: Account Email (Small, dimmed)
- **Search**: "Search by Name, Program, or Email..." placeholder.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Browser test: Search for a specific email address and verify that only campaigns from that account are shown.
- Browser test: Verify that the "Group by Account" toggle correctly organizes the list.

### Manual Verification
- Review the aesthetic quality of the new modal and ensure transitions are smooth.
